## Task: Commit mobile header fix, push, verify deployment

### Context
The mobile header was taking ~50% of the viewport. A hamburger menu has been implemented locally and tested on a 375×812 mobile viewport. Changes are ready to commit.

### Changed files
- `includes/header.html` — Added `nav-toggle` hamburger button, phone link inside nav, separate desktop phone button
- `assets/css/style.css` — Hamburger styles, mobile nav overlay (≤720px), compact logo/brand, `.nav__phone` / `.btn--phone-desktop` visibility toggles
- `assets/js/main.js` — Hamburger toggle logic (aria-expanded, is-open class), auto-close on link tap
- `TODO.md` — Added changelog entry for this fix

### Steps

1. **Run tests**
   ```bash
   bash tests/run-tests.sh
   ```
   Fix any failures before proceeding.

2. **Commit and push**
   ```bash
   git add -A
   git commit -m "fix: compact mobile header with hamburger menu"
   git push
   ```

3. **Wait ~60s for GitHub Pages deployment**, then verify:

4. **Check deployment (mobile)** — open https://schlosserei-maier-ulm.github.io/ with mobile emulation (375×812, touch):
   - [ ] Header is one compact row: logo (small) + brand text + hamburger icon
   - [ ] Hamburger opens vertical nav with all 5 links + phone number
   - [ ] Tapping a nav link closes the menu
   - [ ] Hero section visible without scrolling
   - [ ] No horizontal overflow

5. **Check deployment (desktop)** — same URL without emulation:
   - [ ] Header shows horizontal nav links + phone button (no hamburger)
   - [ ] No visual regressions

6. **Check a subpage** — e.g. https://schlosserei-maier-ulm.github.io/pages/balkone.html on mobile:
   - [ ] Header loads correctly (includes system works)
   - [ ] Hamburger works
   - [ ] Links navigate correctly

7. **Report results** — update `TODO.md` changelog entry status from "Needs commit..." to "Deployed and verified" or note any issues found.
